    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">RGB</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">RGB refers to a system for representing the colors to be used on a computer display. RGB is a combination of Red, Green and Blue. These colors can be combined in various proportions to obtain any color in the visible spectrum.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Each level is measured by the range of decimal numbers from 0 to 255 (256 levels for each color). For example, if a color has zero Blue, it will be a mixture of Red and Green. This means we can generate 256 x 256 x 256 = 16.777.216 different colors with this model.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*ueef5pNNsTIEJoMoPr5tZw.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It is important to note that different devices detect or reproduce a given RGB value differently. An RGB color format is represented by its Red, Green and Blue values, no surprises here:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>RGB = (54, 155, 229)</strong>  |  Note: 54 = Red, 155 = Green and 229 = Blue</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">HEX</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">HEX is a widely known and used format for defining colors on the web. The name comes from the phrase hexadecimal, which is used by humans to shorten binary to a more easily understandable form. Each of the HEX numbers use numbers and letters to represent values between 0–16. Numbers are used for the range 0–9 and letters A, B, C, D, E, F for the range 10–16.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The code itself is a HEX triplet, which represents 3 separate values that specify the levels of the component colors. These 3 values are called bytes and make up a six-digit hexadecimal number used in HTML, CSS, SVG and other computing applications.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The first value pair refers to Red, the second to Green and the third to Blue. One byte represents a number in the range 0 to 255 in decimal notation. In hexadecimal notation, the scale goes from the lowest (00) to the highest (FF) intensity of each color. HEX codes start with a hashtag sign and are followed by the mentioned format:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>HEX = #A3D645</strong>  |  Note: A3 = Red, D6 = Green and 45 = Blue</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">Conversion between RGB & HEX</p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We will transform an RGB code into a HEX code. What this truly means is that we need to convert decimal numbers from given RGB values to hexadecimals. In order to do this, we will divide our values by 16.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span>R / 16 = <strong>X1</strong> + <strong>Y1</strong></span><span>G / 16 = <strong>X2</strong> + <strong>Y2</strong></span><span>B / 16 = <strong>X3</strong> + <strong>Y3</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In the above mentioned formula, X is called the quotient and Y is the remainder. These two numbers are used to represent the HEX value pair for each particular color, Red, Green and Blue. A HEX code can be calculated from these values as <strong>#X1Y1X2Y2X3Y3 </strong>where X1Y1 are the values for Red, X2Y2 for Green and X3Y3 for Blue.<strong> </strong>Let’s have a look at this with the following RGB values:<strong> (54, 155, 229)</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span>R = <strong>54</strong> / 16 = <strong>3 </strong>+<strong> 6</strong></span><span>G = <strong>155</strong> / 16 = <strong>9 </strong>+<strong> 11  </strong>|  Note: 11 = B in hexadecimal</span><span>B = <strong>229</strong> / 16 = <strong>14 </strong>+<strong> 5  </strong>|  Note: 14 = E in hexadecimal</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Voila, our code <strong>(54, 155, 229) in RGB </strong>becomes <strong>#369BE5 in HEX</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We can also make the conversion work in reverse. In case we would like to transform HEX codes into RGB codes, all we have to do is to multiply the quotients by 16 and add the remainders.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span>R = <strong>X1</strong> x 16 + <strong>Y1</strong></span><span>G = <strong>X2</strong> x 16 + <strong>Y2</strong></span><span>B = <strong>X3</strong> x 16 + <strong>Y3</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We already know the quotients (X1, X2, X3) and remainders (Y1, Y2, Y3). A HEX code consists of these values as <strong>#X1Y1X2Y2X3Y3</strong>. Let’s try converting back our HEX code: <strong>#369BE5</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span>R = <strong>3</strong> x 16 + <strong>6</strong> = <strong>54</strong></span><span>G = <strong>9</strong> x 16 + <strong>11</strong> = <strong>155</strong>  |  Note: 11 = B in hexadecimal</span><span>B = <strong>14</strong> x 16 + <strong>5</strong> = <strong>229</strong>  |  Note: 14 = E in hexadecimal</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">There we go, our code <strong>#369BE5 in HEX</strong> becomes <strong>(54, 155, 229) in RGB</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">What do you call friends who like maths?Alge-bros.</p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Keep smiling. We’re off to continue our journey to the world of HSL.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">HSL</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">HSL is a common cylindrical coordinate representation of points in an RGB color model. HSL stands for Hue, Saturation and Luminosity. Hue refers to the colour family of the specific color we’re looking at. It indicates the actual dominant color on the RGB color wheel. Luminosity refers to how much white or black is mixed in the color. Saturation indicates the amount of grey in the same color.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">Conversion between RGB & HSL</p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Luminosity</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Luminosity (also called brightness, lightness or luminance) stands for the intensity of the energy output of a visible light source<em>. </em>It basically tells how light a color is and is measured on the following scale: <strong>L = [0, 1]</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*HGWDGRJe5kzSMZouWvXP8g.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It’s time to introduce the maximum and minimum values among our RGB numbers. <strong>Max(RGB)</strong> stands for the highest and <strong>Min(RGB)</strong> for the lowest value across Red, Green and Blue. In order to make our further calculations work, we need to convert the RGB values to the range 0–1. This can be done by dividing them by 255. Let’s take our existing RGB values for example: <strong>(54, 155, 229)</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>R</strong> = 54 / 255 = <strong>0,212</strong></span><span><strong>G</strong> = 155 / 255 = <strong>0,608</strong></span><span><strong>B</strong> = 229 / 255 = <strong>0,898</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The Luminosity of the RGB color <strong>(54, 155, 229) </strong>can be calculated from the Max(RGB) and Min(RGB) values as follows:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>L</strong> = (1 / 2) x (Max(RGB) + Min(RGB))</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">From our R, G and B numbers, R seems to be the smallest and B the largest. We now know the <strong>Max(RGB) =</strong> <strong>B =</strong> <strong>0,898 </strong>and <strong>Min(RGB) = R = 0,212 </strong>values.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>L</strong> = (1 / 2) x (<!-- -->0,898<!-- --> + <!-- -->0,212<!-- -->) = <strong>0,555 ~ 56%</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Hue</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Most sources of visible light contain energy over a band of wavelengths. Hue is the wavelength within the visible light spectrum at which the energy output from a source is greatest<em>.</em> It<em> </em>is indicated by its position (in degrees) on the RGB color wheel: <strong>H= [0°, 360°]</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*jCZrxJjwBwb_KXQ0JmixIg.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The formula for Hue depends on how RGB values relate to each other. In other words, it depends on which one represents the Max(RGB) and Min(RGB) values.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>(A)</strong> If R ≥ G ≥ B  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [(G-B)/(R-B)]</span><span><strong>(B)</strong> If G &gt; R ≥ B  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [2 - (R-B)/(G-B)]</span><span><strong>(C)</strong> If G ≥ B &gt; R  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [2 + (B-R)/(G-R)]</span><span><strong>(D)</strong> If B &gt; G &gt; R  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [4 - (G-R)/(B-R)]</span><span><strong>(E)</strong> If B &gt; R ≥ G  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [4 + (R-G)/(B-G)]</span><span><strong>(F)</strong> If R ≥ B &gt; G  |  <!-- -->H = <!-- -->60° x [6 - (B-G)/(R-G)]</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The Hue of the RGB color <strong>(54, 155, 229) </strong>can be calculated using the right formula from the pool above. Don’t forget to divide by 255 before going any further.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>R</strong> = 54 / 255 = <strong>0,212</strong></span><span><strong>G</strong> = 155 / 255 = <strong>0,608</strong></span><span><strong>B</strong> = 229 / 255 = <strong>0,898</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>B &gt; G &gt; R</strong> seems to stand true, our match is <strong>(D).</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>H</strong> = <!-- -->60° x [4 - (0,608-0,212)/(0,898-0,212)] = <strong>205,4°</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Saturation</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Saturation is an expression for the relative bandwidth of the visible output from a light source<em>. </em>As saturation increases, colors appear more pure. As saturation decreases, colors appear more washed-out. It is measured on the following scale: <strong>S = [0, 1]</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*8i3YihXj4OB4xKkcwfxFaQ.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The formula for Saturation uses the Min(RGB), Max(RGB) values and Luminosity.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>(A)</strong><em> </em>If L &lt; 1  | <em> </em>S = (Max(RGB) — Min(RGB)) / (1 — |2L - 1|)</span><span><strong>(B)</strong> If L = 1  |  <!-- -->S = 0</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We have calculated the Luminosity before, <strong>L = 0,555. </strong>Our formula will be <strong>(A)</strong> as L = 0,555 &lt; 1. We also know <strong>Max(RGB) =</strong> <strong>0,898 </strong>and <strong>Min(RGB) = 0,212</strong>. We finally have everything we needed for Saturation. Good stuff.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>S</strong> = (<!-- -->0,898<!-- --> — <!-- -->0,212<!-- -->) / (1 — |2 x 0,555 - 1|) = <strong>0</strong><strong>,770 ~ 77%</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*f7rU8GMQ234_69Lx5rWOyw.gif"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">This is you right now.</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">We have successfully calculated Luminosity, Hue and Saturation from a single HEX code</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Now we can define our own rules for accepting colors solely relying on a HEX code. For example, we can set a desired range for the Luminosity or exclude certain colors from the color wheel with Hue. With Saturation we can also influence how washed-out or colorful our screens look.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span><strong>L</strong> = <strong>56%</strong></span><span><strong>H</strong> = <strong>205,4°</strong></span><span><strong>S</strong> = <strong>77%</strong></span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">At Shazam we have decided to only accept colors with a Luminosity value smaller than a certain level (excluding too light ones) and changed this rule for a specific spectrum on the color wheel. This way we could get rid of some bright yellows and greens. By using the conversion formulas in a script, we can also build a simple tool that helps with this process.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">You can download a sample <a href="https://shazam.github.io/colour-picker/" target="_self">Colour Picker</a> using these formulas.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><em>Thanks (and claps) to </em><a style="color:green" href="https://medium.com/u/3738b3d69c93?source=post_page-----90346fb5abda--------------------------------" target="_self">Nikita Kardakov</a><em> for helping with the code.</em></p></div></div></div></section><?php include_once 'Elemental/footer.php'; ?>